Package: uperf-linux-gui
Version: 0.1.0
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Architecture: arm64
Depends: libqt6core6 (>= 6.2), libqt6gui6 (>= 6.2), libqt6qml6 (>= 6.2),
         libqt6quick6 (>= 6.2), libqt6charts6 (>= 6.2), libqt6dbus6 (>= 6.2),
         libglib2.0-0 (>= 2.0), uperf-linux (>= 0.1.0)
Recommends: systemd, jq
Maintainer: code002-2 <hiez832670@gmail.com>
Description: Graphical controller for uperf-linux performance scheduler
 uperf-linux is a userspace CPU/GPU scheduler for Linux ARM64 gaming
 devices. This package includes the Qt6/QML graphical interface that
 allows you to:
  - Switch between Balance, Powersave, and Performance modes
  - Monitor real-time CPU frequencies and loads
  - View detected game processes
  - Tune scheduling thresholds
 .
 The daemon runs as a systemd service and communicates with the GUI
 over DBus.
